headlines.description: Tayler Persons and Tahjai Teague each scored 26 points, Trey Moses poked the ball away from Akron's red-hot Jimond Ivey with four seconds left and Ball State held on for a wild, 111-106 double overtime victory on Saturday, its first series win against...
headlines.shortLinkText: Ball State outlasts Akron, red-hot Ivey 111-106, 2OT

headlines.description: Cameron Young had 15 points, eight rebounds and a career-high eight assists and Andrew Robinson scored 14 points, including four 3-pointers, to help Quinnipiac beat Fairfield 75-70 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young, Robinson help Quinnipiac beat Fairfield 75-70

headlines.description: Jairus Lyles scored seven 3-pointers for 34 points and Maryland-Baltimore County defeated Maine 86-74 Saturday and closed out the RAC Arena on a high note, winning 11 straight at home.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lyles scores 34, UMBC tops Maine 86-74 to close out RAC

headlines.description: Xavier Cooks scored 21 points and Bjorn Broman scored 18 and Winthrop ended the game with a 16-4 run to beat Campbell 75-64 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Winthrop pulls away from Campbell for 75-64 win

headlines.description: D'Marcus Simonds scored eight of his 20 points in the final minute as Georgia State rallied to slip past Texas State 54-50 in a battle for second place in the Sun Belt Conference on Saturday afternoon.
headlines.shortLinkText: Simonds finishes strong as Georgia St. beats Texas St. 54-50

headlines.description: Devin Sibley scored 23 points, John Davis III added 18 with four 3-pointers, and Furman scored a season-high 58 first-half points in its 100-66 blowout of Western Carolina on Saturday to take control of fourth place in Southern Conference play.
headlines.shortLinkText: Furman hits 15 3s in 100-66 rout of  W Carolina

headlines.description: Ryan Kemrite scored 21 points and Liberty downed Presbyterian 81-66 on Saturday afternoon to snap a five-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kemrite with 21 points, Liberty downs Presbyterian 81-66

headlines.description: Ahmad Thomas scored 23 points, MaCio Teague added 21 more and UNC Asheville held off a High Point rally Saturday to get an 84-77 win and move into a tie for first place atop the Big South Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: UNC-Asheville holds off High Point for 84-77 win

headlines.description: Mike Daum tossed in 23 points, including two free throws with 21 seconds left in the game, and South Dakota State hung on for a 78-76 victory over Fort Wayne on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Daum powers South Dakota State to 78-76 win over Fort Wayne

headlines.description: Colton Weisbrod scored 21 points to lead five in double-figure scoring, and Lamar closed on a 10-2 run to beat McNeese 86-80 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lamar closes on 10-2 run, beats McNeese 86-80

headlines.description: Alex Long had 14 points and a career-high 17 rebounds and Steven Whitley scored 12, including the winning layup at the buzzer, to help Norfolk State beat Bethune-Cookman 71-70 on Saturday night for the Wildcats' first loss in Mid-Eastern Athletic...
headlines.shortLinkText: Whitley lifts Norfolk State over Bethune-Cookman 71-70

headlines.description: Shannon Bogues scored 29 points on 9-of-11 shooting and Ty Charles hit 9 of 13 shots and scored 20 to propel Stephen F. Austin to an 82-66 victory over Sam Houston State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen F Austin rolls to 82-66 win over Sam Houston State

headlines.description: David Nichols scored all 14 of his points in the second half, and Albany held Stony Brook to just 18 second-half points for a 57-50 victory on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Albany uses balanced attack to beat Stony Brook 57-50

headlines.description: James Towns had 31 points and Kahlil Dukes scored 28, and Niagara hit a season-high 14 3-pointers to beat Canisius 105-89 on Saturday night and knock the Griffins from first place in the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Niagara hits 15 3s, beats Canisius 105-89

headlines.description: Zach Johnson scored 18 points, Bandon Goodwin scored 16 and Florida Gulf Coast defeated Jacksonville 68-62 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: FGCU closes with 8-0 run to beat Jacksonville 68-62

headlines.description: Francis Alonso scored 24 points on eight 3-pointers and led five players in double-figure scoring as UNC Greensboro beat Samford 98-82 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Alonso with 8 3-pointers, UNC Greensboro beats Samford 98-82

headlines.description: Joseph Kilgore finished with the first triple double in school history as he scored eight of his 24 points in overtime to help Texas A&M-Corpus Christi beat Houston Baptist 79-69 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kilgore has Texas A&M-CC's 1st triple double in OT victory

headlines.description: Curtis Phillips scored 17 points and Tennessee Tech made 10 of 16 free throws in the final five minutes to defeat Tennessee-Martin 63-55 on Saturday night after blowing an 18-point second-half lead.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tenn Tech recovers to hold off UT Martin 63-55

headlines.description: Jerrick Harding scored 22 points, Zach Braxton got his fourth double-double of the season and Weber State held off Idaho State for a 77-70 win Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harding, Braxton lead Weber State past Idaho State 77-70

headlines.description: Victor Sanders scored 26 points, Brayon Blake added 24 and Idaho rolled to a 96-71 victory over North Dakota on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sanders, Blake lead Idaho past North Dakota 96-71

headlines.description: Kyle Allman scored a career-high 40 points, Austen Awosika made two free throws with 11.4 seconds left and Cal State Fullerton rallied to defeat Hawaii 69-66 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Allman scores 40, Fullerton edges Hawaii 69-66

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
